  "interpretation": {
    "supported_claim": "On this machine and the recorded one-million-cell targeted-upsert workloads, requested compression level materially changed Patch save CPU, wall time and output size. Level 1 was the throughput-oriented setting among the measured levels; level 9 was not justified for the numeric workload and remained expensive for mixed inline strings.",
    "public_policy": "The public default is unchanged. Compression level remains caller-controlled because the acceptable CPU versus output-size tradeoff is workload-specific.",
